SsApiRc SsHandler::ActivateCallForwarding (  const InputParser::SsCode  code,
const PhoneNumber &  forward_to_no,
const InputParser::BasicServiceMmiCode  bs = InputParser::AllServices,
const WString &  time = L""
)  const
 

Activates a specific call forwarding feature defined by the supplementary service code, for one or all basic services.

Parameters:
code Defines the supplementary service CFU, CFBusy, CFNoReply, CFNotReachable, AllCF or AllConditionalCF.
forward_to_no The phone number where the call is fowarded to.
bs Defines the basic service which is AllServices, AllTeleServices, Telephony, AllDataServices, FacsimileServices, ShortMessageServices, AllTeleServicesExceptSMS, VoiceGroupCallService, VoiceBroadcastService, AllBearerServices, AllAsyncServices, AllSyncServices, AllDataCircuitSync, AllDataCircuitAsync,AllGPRSBearerServices.
time Defines the time for that a "CFNoReply" call is waiting until the call will be forwarded This param is just possible for CFNoReply, AllCF or AllConditionalCF but it is not necessary.

BOOLEAN SsHandler::IsSsPending (   )  const
 

Returns TRUE if a supplementary service transaction is currently pending, FALSE otherwise.

Returns:
Success - if MN accepted supplementary service request, SupplementaryServicePending if another supplementary service is currently pending, SupplementaryServiceDenied if the supplementary service request was rejected by MN.

See SendControlString before. Avoids obsolete implicit WString constructor calls if called with L"code".

SsApiRc SsHandler::SendControlString (  const WString &  code  )  const
 

Sends a supplementary service control string to the network. and (actively) waits until MN accepts or rejects the request. The string format has to be as defined in GSM 2.30 (e.g. #31# for CLIR interrogation).

Parameters:
code WString, conform to GSM 2.30 denoting the supplementary service request.
Returns:
Success - if MN accepted supplementary service request, SupplementaryServicePending if another supplementary service is currently pending, SupplementaryServiceDenied if the supplementary service request was rejected by MN.

SsApiRc SsHandler::SendDetectedError (  const SsErrorCode::Code  error_code  )  const
 

Sends an error code to the network in order to indicate, that the USS request or -notify cannot be handeled correctly by the MS,

Returns:
Success - if successfully canceled, SupplementaryServiceNotPending, if no pending supplementary service request found, InvalidTipd if referred request has an invalid TIPD

SsApiRc SsHandler::SendPasswordResponse (  const WString &  password  )  const
 

Sends a required password to the network, after the network requested for it with a PasswordInquiryMsg. This happens for example during the execution of a supplemntary service related to call barring.

Returns:
Success - if successfully canceled, SupplementaryServiceNotPending, if no pending supplementary service request found, InvalidTipd if referred request has an invalid TIPD

SsApiRc SsHandler::TerminateSupplementaryService (   )  const
 

Cancels a sent supplementary service request.

Returns:
